Here's a prioritised list of what to tackle next:

1. User Management — Create & Invite Users
Right now the Security Admin page can assign roles to existing users, but there's no way to create new users from the UI. You need a "Invite User" flow: an admin enters an email, the backend creates the account (or sends an invite email), and the user sets their password on first login. This is the most critical gap — RBAC is useless if you can't onboard users without direct DB access.

2. Invoice Creation from the UI
The invoice list page shows invoices but there's no "Create Invoice" button wired to a real customer selector. The CreateInvoiceModal exists but needs to be connected to a customer search/select so users can actually create invoices end-to-end without hitting the API directly.

3. Refresh Token / Session Persistence
Currently JWT tokens expire and the user gets silently signed out. You need a refresh token flow: store a long-lived refresh token (httpOnly cookie), and silently re-issue the access token before it expires. Without this, any user working for more than the token TTL gets kicked out mid-session.

4. Audit Log
Any RBAC system needs an audit trail. Every time a role is assigned/removed, a permission is changed, or a security object is toggled, that action should be logged with who did it and when. This is a backend table + a read-only Audit tab on the Security Admin page.

5. Dashboard Enhancements
The current dashboard shows 5 static metrics. Useful additions:

Date range filter (last 30/90 days, custom range)
Overdue invoices list inline (not just the total amount)
Cashflow trend chart (monthly inflow/outflow over time)
6. Email Notifications
The reminder engine logs to console (LoggingNotificationService) but never actually sends emails. Wire up a real email provider (SendGrid, Resend, or SMTP) so payment reminders actually reach customers.

7. Payments Module Visibility
The PAYMENTS security object exists in the RBAC schema but there's no Payments page in the UI. Either build a standalone payments list page or remove the object from the seed data to avoid confusion.

8. Reports Module
Same situation as Payments — REPORTS is seeded as a security object but there's no Reports page. Either scaffold a basic reports page (export invoices to CSV, payment summary by date range) or clean up the orphaned permission.

9. End-to-End / Integration Tests
The backend has unit and property tests but no end-to-end tests covering the full HTTP stack with a real database. Adding a test project using WebApplicationFactory with a test Postgres container (Testcontainers) would catch regressions across the API surface.

10. Error Boundary + Loading States Polish
Several pages show a blank screen while permissions load (the PermissionRoute returns null during loading). A proper skeleton/loading state and a React error boundary would make the app feel more production-ready and prevent white-flash on navigation.
